JEN BEN ON, etc., Appellant, v. UNITED STATES of America, Appellee. No. 8898. Circuit Court of Appeals, Ninth Circuit. July 25, 1938. Stephen M. White, of San Francisco, Cal., for appellant. , Frank J. Hennessy, U. S. Atty., of San Francisco, Cal., for appellee.

Before DENMAN, MATHEWS, and STEPHENS, Circuit Judges.

PER CURIAM.

Upon consideration of the stipulation of counsel for respective parties, and good cause therefor appearing, ordered appeal in above cause dismissed, that a decree of dismissal be filed and entered accordingly, and that the mandate of this court in this cause issue forthwith.
